name: TIPS 230302 — Data Center Hosting, Sales and Service
description: Cooperative purchasing agreement managed by The Interlocal Purchasing System (TIPS), competitively solicited and awarded by Region 8 Education Service Center (Texas) for data center hosting, sales and service across the full Rackspace Technology portfolio; three-year term per TIPS Vendor Agreement standard terms

name: TIPS 230105 — Technology Solutions Products and Services
description: Cooperative purchasing agreement managed by TIPS, competitively solicited and awarded by Region 8 Education Service Center for technology solutions products and services available to government, education, and public entities nationwide; three-year term per TIPS Vendor Agreement standard terms

name: DIR-CPO-5186 — Texas DIR Cloud Services
description: Cloud cooperative services contract awarded May 30, 2023 by Texas Department of Information Resources for IaaS, PaaS, MaaS, Cloud Broker and Related Services; announced via GlobeNewswire press release; DIR exercised automatic renewal extending contract through May 8, 2027 per dir.texas.gov

name: DIR-CPO-5004 — Texas DIR DBITS
description: Deliverables-Based Information Technology Services (DBITS) contract awarded by Texas DIR covering Application Development, Maintenance, Support, Upgrade, Migration, Transformation, and ERP; services only, no hardware or software; DIR exercised automatic renewal extending contract through December 21, 2025 per dir.texas.gov

name: DIR-CPO-5155 — Texas DIR AI Services
description: Artificial Intelligence services contract awarded by Texas DIR covering AI, Machine Learning, RPA, NLP, Computer Vision, and Digital Assistant technologies; started March 5, 2025 per dir.texas.gov; current term through March 5, 2027 with renewals through March 5, 2030; services only, no resellers; pricing at 20% off MSRP

name: Equalis Group R10-1111C — IaaS and PaaS Cloud Solutions
description: National cooperative purchasing agreement for IaaS and PaaS cloud solutions, competitively solicited via RFP issued January 29, 2021 by Region 10 Education Service Center (Equalis Group Lead Agency), addressed to Mr. Clint Pechacek; Rackspace awarded as lowest responsive and responsible bidder; available to public sector and non-profit entities nationwide via Equalis Group membership

name: NCPA/OMNIA Partners 01-167 — IT Storage, Security and Managed Services
description: National cooperative purchasing agreement for IT Storage, IT Security and Managed Services competitively solicited and awarded September 5, 2023 by Region 14 Education Service Center; managed by NCPA (National Cooperative Purchasing Alliance), a wholly-owned subsidiary of OMNIA Partners; accommodates adding any Rackspace Technology service before purchase order submission

name: Rhode Island MPA-308 — National Cooperative Contract
description: State of Rhode Island national cooperative contract covering the full Rackspace Technology portfolio available to government entities; contract reference MPA-308 / number 3806796; also referenced with California CMAS 3-22-06-1050; specific contract dates not confirmed in publicly available sources

name: FLFO Term Loan Facility
description: First lien first out senior secured term loan facility established March 12, 2024 as part of the March 2024 Refinancing Transactions under the New First Lien Credit Agreement; borrower is Rackspace Finance, LLC; exact principal amount disclosed in FY2024 10-K XBRL data; part of total debt principal of approximately $2,504M as of June 2025

name: FLSO Term Loan Facility
description: First lien second out senior secured term loan facility established March 12, 2024; Apollo Global Management affiliate holds a portion of outstanding principal per FY2024 10-K; part of March 2024 Refinancing Transactions; interest rate steps down over time per indenture terms

name: 3.50% FLSO Senior Secured Notes due 2028
description: First lien second out senior secured notes bearing 3.50% interest, issued March 12, 2024 as part of Refinancing Transactions; approximately $480M outstanding per Q2 2025 10-Q disclosure; governed by 3.50% FLSO Senior Secured Notes Indenture; interest payable semiannually; due 2028

name: 5.375% Senior Notes due 2028
description: Senior unsecured notes bearing 5.375% interest, originally issued December 1, 2020; governed by the 5.375% Notes Indenture; partially exchanged and repurchased during 2024 Refinancing Transactions per FY2024 10-K

name: New Revolving Credit Facility
description: Senior secured first lien first out revolving credit facility with $375 million commitment, established March 12, 2024 replacing the prior Revolving Credit Facility as part of Refinancing Transactions per FY2024 10-K

name: Receivables Purchase Facility
description: Accounts receivable purchase agreement entered September 29, 2023 with PNC Bank, National Association; utilizes Rackspace Receivables II, LLC as special purpose vehicle for receivables factoring per FY2024 10-K

name: Apollo Global Management Leveraged Buyout Agreement
description: Leveraged buyout of Rackspace Hosting, Inc. (now Rackspace Technology Global, Inc.) by Inception Parent, Inc., an Apollo Global Management investment vehicle, completed November 3, 2016 for approximately $4.3 billion; transaction took the company private until re-IPO in August 2020 per FY2024 10-K

name: Master Economic Incentives Agreement (MEIA)
description: Economic incentives agreement associated with Rackspace corporate headquarters in San Antonio; original value undisclosed; early-terminated in March 2024 in connection with sale of corporate headquarters facility, incurring a $9.0 million early termination fee per FY2024 earnings press release and 10-K

name: Seattle Children's Hospital 10-Year Managed Cloud Agreement
description: Ten-year managed cloud services agreement with Seattle Children's Hospital for comprehensive cloud infrastructure management; announced in early 2025 Rackspace case study materials; one of the longest publicly disclosed customer service agreements; exact start and end dates not confirmed, approximate based on announcement timing

name: Palantir Technologies Strategic Partnership Agreement
description: Strategic technology partnership for Rackspace to provide governed managed operations running Palantir Foundry and AIP in production environments including security, compliance and managed operations from edge; announced February 18, 2026 via GlobeNewswire targeting regulated industries including healthcare, financial services, and government; partnership term not publicly disclosed, end date approximate

name: Texas DIR DCS Public Cloud Manager Services
description: Contract awarded by Texas Department of Information Resources to Rackspace US, Inc. for Data Center Services Public Cloud Manager providing cloud computing operational, technical and security services; confirmed via dir.texas.gov vendor page listing for Rackspace US, Inc.; exact contract dates and number approximate pending DIR contract document verification

name: NCPA 01-85 — Data Storage, Cloud, Converged and Data Protection
description: National cooperative purchasing agreement for data storage, cloud, converged and data protection awarded December 3, 2018 by Region 14 Education Service Center; five-year term through November 30, 2023 with zero renewal options; superseded by NCPA 01-167 (ctr-007) awarded September 5, 2023; source: ncpa.us/Vendors/Rackspace

name: California CMAS 3-22-06-1050 — Multiple Award Schedule
description: California Multiple Award Schedule (CMAS) contract referenced on Rackspace government contracts page for Rhode Island and national accessibility; CMAS number 3-22-06-1050; enables California state and local government procurement of Rackspace services; specific scope and dates not confirmed in publicly available sources

name: AWS Strategic Collaboration Agreement (SCA) — October 2024
description: Multi-year Strategic Collaboration Agreement (SCA) signed between Rackspace Technology and Amazon Web Services in October 2024. Covers advisory services, application and infrastructure migration, modernization, data, machine learning, and generative AI solutions across Rackspace's full customer base. Deepens the AWS-Rackspace partnership beyond reseller terms to include joint go-to-market, co-sell, and co-investment obligations. Rackspace cited this agreement as a catalyst for the Public Cloud segment growth strategy in FY2025 guidance. Source: ir.rackspace.com press release October 2024; Rackspace 10-K FY2024 Item 1.

name: Rubrik Cyber Recovery Partnership and Reseller Agreement — 2024
description: Reseller and joint go-to-market agreement between Rackspace Technology and Rubrik, Inc. covering the Rackspace Cyber Recovery powered by Rubrik solution. Rackspace bundles Rubrik Enterprise Edition backup and Rubrik Security Cloud with its Immutable Recovery Environment (IRE) to deliver Cyber Recovery as a managed service offering. Solution targets ransomware recovery use cases with air-gapped, immutable backups and SLA-backed recovery times. Available to Rackspace managed cloud customers across AWS and private cloud segments. Source: Rackspace newsroom Cyber Recovery product announcement; Rubrik partner directory.

name: UK G-Cloud 14 Framework — Rackspace Technology Appointment
description: UK Crown Commercial Service (CCS) G-Cloud 14 Digital Marketplace framework appointment for Rackspace Technology UK Limited. Covers IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS cloud services including Rackspace Government Cloud on AWS and Rackspace Managed Cloud Platform for UK public sector customers. Current lot services include cloud hosting (Lot 1), software (Lot 2), and support (Lot 3). G-Cloud 14 framework ran from May 2023; superseded by G-Cloud 14 refresh. Source: Crown Commercial Service Digital Marketplace; Rackspace UK public sector listings; cust-049 through cust-051 UK government customer relationships.

name: Apollo Global Management Portfolio Governance Framework
description: Ongoing governance and reporting framework established under Apollo Global Management's leveraged buyout of Rackspace Technology (completed November 2016, per ctr-015). Apollo holds approximately 58% of Rackspace's outstanding shares as of FY2024. Framework governs board representation rights (Apollo nominates majority of board seats), information rights, anti-dilution protections, registration rights, and reporting obligations to Apollo affiliates. Rackspace is required to provide Apollo with non-public financial information under the governance framework. Source: Rackspace 10-K FY2024 Related Party Transactions section; SEC proxy statement FY2024.

name: GSA Multiple Award Schedule (MAS) — IT Professional Services SIN 54151S
description: U.S. General Services Administration Multiple Award Schedule (formerly IT Schedule 70) under Special Item Number 54151S — Information Technology Professional Services. Authorizes Rackspace Technology Inc. to sell cloud professional services, managed services, and cloud advisory to all U.S. federal agencies. Required for federal civilian and DoD agency procurement. Referenced in FedRAMP authorized service listings. Source: GSA eBuy and GSA Advantage procurement portal.

name: SEWP V (Solutions for Enterprise-Wide Procurement) — CIO-SP3 Cloud Services
description: NASA SEWP V Government-Wide Acquisition Contract authorizing Rackspace to sell cloud infrastructure, managed services, and technology solutions to all federal government agencies. SEWP V is NASA's premier IT products and services GWAC. Rackspace is listed as a SEWP V authorized reseller via team arrangements. Used for procurement by DoD, intelligence community, and civilian agencies.

name: Crown Commercial Service (CCS) Technology Services 3 (TS3) — RM6161
description: UK Crown Commercial Service Technology Services 3 framework (RM6161) appointing Rackspace Technology UK Limited as approved supplier for managed service provision, cloud hosting, and IT outsourcing across UK central government and public sector. Covers Lot 1 (end-to-end IT managed services) and Lot 2 (IT managed services). Serves UK Cabinet Office, Ministry of Justice, Department for Transport, and NHS customers documented in this graph.

name: NASPO ValuePoint Cloud Solutions Master Agreement — AR2515
description: NASPO ValuePoint (National Association of State Procurement Officials) Cloud Solutions Master Agreement AR2515. Multi-state cooperative contract enabling all 50 state governments, localities, and educational institutions to procure Rackspace cloud services without separate competitive bid. One of the most widely used state and local government IT procurement vehicles. Rackspace listed as participating vendor.

name: VMware Enterprise License Agreement (ELA) — Broadcom Transition
description: VMware Enterprise License Agreement (ELA) post-Broadcom acquisition of VMware (February 2024). Covers Rackspace private cloud infrastructure licensing for VMware vSphere, vSAN, NSX, and vCenter across Rackspace-owned and managed data centers. Rackspace is a VMware Cloud Verified provider. Broadcom subscription licensing transition creates material cost risk disclosed in Rackspace 10-K. Agreement governs Rackspace Private Cloud powered by VMware product line.

name: Florida DMS State Term Contract — Cloud Computing Services
description: Florida Department of Management Services (DMS) State Term Contract for Cloud Computing Services, authorizing Rackspace to provide IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS managed cloud services to Florida state agencies, counties, municipalities, and qualifying institutions. Rackspace listed on Florida cloud services term contract. Complements federal TIPS and DIR cooperative purchasing vehicles already in graph.

name: Cisco Enterprise Agreement — Networking and Security
description: Cisco Enterprise Agreement covering Cisco networking hardware, software subscriptions, and security products for Rackspace data center infrastructure. Covers Cisco Catalyst switching, Nexus data center networking, ASA/Firepower security appliances, and Cisco DNA software licensing. Rackspace is a Cisco Gold Certified Partner and Cloud Platform & Managed Services specialist. Enterprise Agreement structure provides volume pricing and simplified licensing across Rackspace's global DC footprint.

name: Microsoft Cloud Solution Provider (CSP) & Azure Expert MSP Agreement
description: Microsoft Cloud Solution Provider (CSP) Indirect Reseller agreement and Azure Expert Managed Service Provider (MSP) designation for Rackspace Technology. Azure Expert MSP is Microsoft's highest partner designation requiring third-party audit of Azure managed service capabilities. Rackspace achieved Azure Expert MSP status. Enables resale of Azure licenses with managed services margin, Microsoft co-sell eligibility, and Microsoft Marketplace listing. Governs Rackspace Microsoft Copilot Services and Microsoft 365 Managed products.

name: Google Cloud Partner Program — Premier Partner and MSP Agreement
description: Google Cloud Partner Advantage Program agreement designating Rackspace as a Premier Services Partner with Managed Service Provider specialization. Authorizes Rackspace to resell Google Cloud Platform services, earn partner incentives, and co-sell with Google Cloud sales teams. Rackspace Google Workspace Managed and GCP managed operations services governed under this agreement. Rackspace achieved Google Cloud MSP designation per published partner directory.

name: AWS Premier Tier Services Partner Agreement — SCA Supplement
description: AWS Premier Tier Consulting Partner agreement governing Rackspace status as an AWS Premier Consulting Partner and AWS Managed Service Provider (MSP). Rackspace holds multiple AWS competency designations (Financial Services, Healthcare, Government, Migration). This agreement underpins the broader Strategic Collaboration Agreement (ctr-022, Oct 2024) and governs partner-led co-sell, marketplace listing rights, and training commitments. Rackspace was one of the original AWS MSP program charter members (2012).

name: Equinix IBX Data Center Colocation Master Services Agreement
description: Master Services Agreement with Equinix Inc. governing Rackspace colocation, power, and cross-connect services across multiple Equinix International Business Exchange (IBX) data centers globally. Covers Equinix sites mapped as IX facility sites in this graph (site-050 through site-059). Equinix is Rackspace's primary third-party colocation and interconnection provider. Agreement covers cage space, cross-connects, meet-me rooms, and remote hands services.

name: Oracle Partner Network (OPN) — Cloud and License Agreement
description: Oracle Partner Network agreement designating Rackspace as an Oracle Certified Partner with Managed Services specialization. Governs Rackspace's Oracle-on-cloud managed services offering including Oracle Database on AWS (RDS, self-managed), Oracle E-Business Suite migrations, and Oracle licensing advisory. Rackspace has Oracle ACE and Oracle Cloud consulting competency. Agreement covers resale rights, support obligations, and co-marketing terms for Oracle workload migrations.
